THE GAME
--------

  'Toptile' is a Workbench game where the goal is to move all the
shapes that appear on hexagonal tiles, so they are placed at the
top of a pyramidal game board. When a shape is placed at the top
of the board, it is replaced by a 'neutral' shape. You get 1 point
for each (non neutral) shape that is placed at the top. If you
consecutively place several shapes of the same type at the top,
you get more points...

  To complicate matters a little, only a small portion of the game
board is displayed at all time. So you have to move on the game
board in order to fetch the needed shapes and move them to the
top. Additionnally, the shapes must be moved by following the
links that are placed between the hexagonal tiles, and some game
boards are more complex to find your way in than in others...

  Have fun!

